The key insight for this US: the **batching infrastructure already exists** (StaticInstances + StructureInstances/FenceInstances/PropInstances) but the components were **never wired into the game scene**. Draw calls scale with unique model × sub-mesh combinations, not entity count — so wiring these in reduces N structure draw calls to M unique-model draw calls where M << N.

