Now add `matrixAutoUpdate = false` to the InstancedMesh in `StaticInstances.tsx`:

`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`

Three.js calls `updateWorldMatrix()` on every object every frame by default. For InstancedMesh objects sitting at the scene origin (position is always `[0,0,0]` — instances are positioned via `setMatrixAt()`), this is pure waste. Setting `matrixAutoUpdate = false` skips the decompose-recompose cycle for a static world matrix, saving ~6 multiplications per InstancedMesh per frame.

`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`
